# RBAC Monitoring Views

## Configuration

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Monitoring Warehouse** | `{{ rbac_monitoring_warehouse | upper }}` |
{%- if rbac_audit_scope == 'Specific Data Products' %}
| **Scope** | Specific Data Products |
| **Target Prefixes** | {{ rbac_target_prefixes | join(', ') }} |
{%- else %}
| **Scope** | Full Account |
{%- endif %}

## Views Created

All views are created in `RBAC_MONITORING.VIEWS`:

| # | View | Purpose |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | `V_ROLE_MEMBERSHIP` | Current role assignments for all users |
| 2 | `V_PRIVILEGE_CHANGES` | Grant and revoke history over time |
| 3 | `V_DIRECT_USER_GRANTS` | Direct user grants (RBAC bypasses — should be empty) |
| 4 | `V_ROLE_HIERARCHY_DEPTH` | Role chain depth with health status |
| 5 | `V_USER_ACTIVITY` | User login activity and dormancy detection |

## Health Checks

After creating the views, verify these health indicators:

| View | Healthy State |
|------|--------------|
| V_DIRECT_USER_GRANTS | **Zero rows** |
| V_ROLE_HIERARCHY_DEPTH | All roles at **HEALTHY** (depth ≤ 4) |
| V_USER_ACTIVITY | No **DORMANT** users with active roles |

## Access

- Views are readable by SECURITYADMIN
- Monitoring queries use warehouse `{{ rbac_monitoring_warehouse | upper }}`

